na]]\n| [[Denisa Kola]]  \n| Unplaced\n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF99; \"\n| [[Miss Universe 2002|2002]]\n| [[Tirana]]\n| [[Anisa Kospiri]] \n| Top 10\n| \n|-\n| [[Miss Universe 2000|2000]]\n| [[Shkod\u00ebr]]\n| [[Gentiana Ramadani]] \n| Unplaced\n| \n|-\n| [[Miss Universe 1999|1999]]\n| [[Prishtina]]\n| [[Venera Mustafa]]\n| Unplaced\n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF99; \"\n| [[Miss Universe 1995|1995]]\n| [[Durr\u00ebs]]\n| [[Hygerta Sako]]\n| Top 10\n| \n|-\n| [[Miss Universe 1994|1994]]\n| [[Tirana]]\n| Ilda Reka\n| Unplaced\n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF99; \"\n| [[Miss Universe 1993|1993]]\n| [[Kor\u00e7\u00eb]]\n| [[Monika Zguro]] \n| Top 5\n| \n|-\n| [[Miss Universe 1992|1992]]\n| [[Kruj\u00eb]]\n| [[Sidorela Kola]]\n| Unplaced\n| \n|-\n| [[Miss Universe 1991|1991]]\n| [[Tirana]]\n| [[Valbona Selimllari]]\n|\n| \n|-\n|}\n\n===Miss World===\n[[File:Miss Albania 07 Elda Dushi.jpg|160px|thumb|right|Elda Dushi, Miss World Albania 2007]]\n\n<poem>\n{{Color box|gold|border=black}} \u2013 Winner\n{{Color box|#FFFF66|border=black}} \u2013 Finalist\n{{Color box|#FFFF99|border=black}} \u2013 Semifinalist\n</poem>\nFrom 2016 to 2018, the first runner-up of Miss Universe Albania has been sent to [[Miss World]]. Prior, they were either appointed through an internal selection, or a winner or runner-up of Miss Albania was sent. Since 2018, Miss World Albania has been selected independent of Miss Universe Albania.\n{| class=\"wikitable \" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n!width=\"60\"|Year\n!width=\"100\"|Municipality\n!width=\"250\"|Miss World Albania\n!width=\"150\"|Placement at Miss World\n!width=\"100\"|Special awards\n|-\n| [[Miss World 2020|2020]] \n| TBA\n| TBA\n| TBA\n| \n|-\n| [[Miss World 2019|2019]] \n| [[Tirana]]\n| Atalanta Kercyku (Appointed)\n| Unplaced\n| \n|-\n| [[Miss World 2018|2018]] \n| [[Tirana]]\n| Nikita Preka (Appointed)\n| Unplaced\n| \n|-\n| [[Miss World 2017|2017]] \n| [[Berat]]\n| Joana Grabolli<ref>{{cite web |url=